            <p class="py-2">
              Nav links and nav items can be sized using different classes. You can apply sizes
              directly to nav-links using <code>nav-link-*</code> classes or to nav-items using <code
                >nav-item-*</code
              > classes, where * can be xs, sm, lg, or xl.
            </p>

            <!-- Navbar Sizing Example -->
            <ComponentPreview
              title="Navigation Link Sizes"
              height="400px"
              component={navLinkSizeVeriations}
              htmlCode={navLinkSizeVeriations}
            />
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="brand">Brand</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
              The <code>navbar-brand</code> class in Bootstrap is used to define the branding or logo
              section of a navbar, typically linking to the homepage or main site.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="my-3">
            <h3 class="mb-0" id="text">Text</h3>
            <p class="py-2">
