              like <code>navbar-expand-*</code>
              (e.g., <code>navbar-expand-lg</code>), which control when the navbar should collapse.
              The <code>navbar-toggler</code>
              class creates a button to toggle the navbar on smaller screens, while <code
                >navbar-collapse</code
              > manages the collapsible content. These elements work together to create a navbar that
              is horizontally displayed on large screens and collapses into a toggleable menu on smaller
              ones.
            </p>
          </div>
